<p>
<seg id=1> On the World AIDS Day, US president Clinton guaranteed to provide new aids to prevent this kind of fatal disease. This will include providing more financial aid for reseach. </seg>
<seg id=2> Clinton planned to increase the AIDS research funds with 30 percent for the National Health Research Institute. </seg>
<seg id=3> He also planned to declare the 10 million US dollars financial aid for taking care of AIDS orphans. </seg>
<seg id=4> The Clinton government showed that the increase for research funds this time was the biggest once-only investment for AIDS research from the US Public Funds. </seg>
</p>
